{"article_id":"DLLqLnzcvkisbKKd","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Trump ' s second attempt at a travel ban was supposed to avoid the legal challenges","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"faced by his first travel ban .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"But the latest iteration of the executive order has itself been blocked in several courts ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"with the latest attack coming in a public rebuke from a Richmond-based federal appeals court .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The 4th Circuit Court of Appeals not only refused to reinstate Trump ' s temporary ban on nationals from six majority-Muslim countries from entering the United States ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"but also dressed down the government in its decision","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"for asking the court to `` blindly refer to executive power '' and uphold an order","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that `` drips with religious intolerance , animus and discrimination . ''","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"The administration is now waiting for a ruling from the 9th Circuit Court of Appeals ,","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"with court watchers saying","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"that the chances","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"of Trump prevailing in a court","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"that ruled against his first order","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"are slim to none .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"The Department of Justice has already announced its plan","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"to appeal to the Supreme Court ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"but even conservatives aren ' t sure","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"the court will take the case","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"without a lower circuit court split .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Only one court , a Virginia district court , upheld Trump ' s revised order .","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"\" If the 9th Circuit issues an opinion","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and there ' s no circuit split ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"there ' s the distinct possibility","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"the court will decide not to take the case , \"","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"said Josh Blackman , a constitutional law professor at the South Texas College of Law in Houston and a member of the conservative Federalist Society .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"\" It would be insane ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"because there have been so many errors","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"made in the lower court . \"","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"But Blackman said","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"the high court refused to take the case","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"challenging same-sex marriage","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"until at least one lower court had ruled","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"that it was lawful ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"creating a split .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Even without a lower court split ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Blackman claims","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"the government has a number of options","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"to choose from","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"on how to proceed .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"\" The government said","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"they want to appeal to the Supreme Court ,","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"but they didn ' t say when , \"","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"\" The statement was somewhat open-ended . \"","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"He claims","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"the administration could seek a rehearing in the 9th Circuit","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"``","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"not if , but","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"when they lose , ''","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"petition for a Supreme Court review of the 4th Circuit ' s decision now ,","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"ask the Supreme Court for an emergency stay of that ruling","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"or ask concurrently for a stay and for the court to take its case .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"if the court were to take the government ' s case ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"liberals say","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"it ' s going to be tough to persuade Justice Anthony Kennedy","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"- the high court ' s regular swing voter -","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"to rule in Trump ' s favor .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Carl Tobias , a professor of law at the University of Richmond School of Law , noted","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"that the 4th Circuit used Kennedy ' s concurring opinion in a 2015 immigration case","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"to defend its 10-3 decision","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"to break with court precedent","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"and consider Trump ' s campaign statements","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"about banning all Muslims","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"in finding the order discriminatory .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"The majority said","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"Kennedy explained in Kerry v. Din","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"when a plaintiff makes \" an affirmative showing of bad faith \"","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"that is \" plausibly alleged with sufficient particularity , \"","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"courts may \" look behind \" the challenged action","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"to assess its \" facially legitimate \" justification .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"But Judge Paul Niemeyer claimed in his dissent","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"that the majority \" relied on a scattershot string of quotations \"","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"to \" conceal the decisions ' faithful application \" of court precedent","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"that prevents the court from considering Trump ' s remarks .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Blackman called the majority ' s reference to Kennedy 's opinion \" borderline disingenuous . \"","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Hans von Spakovsky , a senior legal fellow at the Heritage Foundation , argued","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"that the Supreme Court could easily strike down the 4th Circuit ' s ruling .","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"\" You get the bias","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"that basically poisons the opinion","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"when you read the first page","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"when [ Judge Roger ] Gregory says","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"the executive order in ' context drips with religious intolerance , animus and discrimination. ' Excuse my language ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"but that is bullshit , \"","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"\" You can read the executive order from front to back .","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"There isn ' t anything in there","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"that authorizes any government agency to discriminate on the basis of religion . \"","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"Von Spakovsky said","depth":3},{"id":90,"text":"he 's hopeful","depth":5},{"id":91,"text":"the court will side with the administration","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"and \" slam \" the lower courts","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"for ruling against the president .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"\" That ' s what needs to happen , \"","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"\" They need to get slammed","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"for not following previous Supreme Court precedent","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"and they should also be slammed in essence","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"for substituting their judgment for that of the president on national security issues . \"","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"But not everyone ' s expecting the case to reach the high court .","depth":3},{"id":101,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"the Supreme Court will want to hear this case","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"unless they want to affirm it , ''","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"said Reaz Jafri , an immigration lawyer","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"who heads the global immigration practice at Withersworldwide .","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"Jafri argued","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"the case is already moot","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"since the revised 90-day ban would have ended Saturday .","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"\" It ' s been proven there is no emergency ,","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"so why not let Congress go back and legislate the issue of vetting ? \"","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"he said .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":223,"left":200,"right":222,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":125,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":119,"right":124,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":115,"right":118,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":113,"right":114,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":113,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":4,"right":117,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":117,"left":5,"right":116,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":8,"right":123,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":9,"right":122,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":122,"left":121,"right":13,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":10,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":144,"right":198,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":130,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":129,"right":19,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":126,"right":128,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":126,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":16,"right":127,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent"